Since it was January, I "grilled" these indoors on a grill pan. Smoked up the house a little. They had good flavor but I think I'd just roast them in the oven next time.

Rating: 1
As written, these were super bland. Really, no one at our Thanksgiving would have eaten them. But we changed a 1 fork recipe into a 4 fork recipe with some ingenuity when we realized that we had used up all of our sweet potatoes on this recipe!!! We combined maple syrup, white balsamic vinegar, rice vinegar, sriracha, and pick-a-peppa sauce and tossed the fries with that strange brew. Then, we reheated the whole mess when we got to my mom's house. It was a total hit. I am so glad we made this recipe because it took us down the road to invention and savory enjoyment!

Rating: 4
These were awesome. Followed recipe exactly and fries turned out perfectly. Loved the bit of char on the fries from grilling which made them crispy. Served with steak and tomatoes... rave reviews!

Rating: 1
