Rating: 4
These got rave reviews from my husband, who is a huge fan of sweet potato fries when we go out. The 2nd time I made these, I made 2 changes which made them much better: 1. For "salting & peppering to taste", I used garlic salt. 2. I baked them in a single layer on a cookie sheet in the oven instead of on the grill (where I found it really hard not to burn them). I baked them at 375 for about 20 mins, then cranked it up to 425 to make them a little crisper, taking them out from time to time to turn them over.

Rating: 4
I love the crispy charred spots on the outside with the creamy sweet potato flavor inside and spicy cayenne.

Rating: 4
These fries are awesome! I baked them (as it was snowing outside), and they turned out very well. Would make them again with a turkey burger or grilled chicken.

Rating: 4
