Rating: 4
Anything this easy and tasty is a definite repeat dish for me. I baked mine, since I already had the oven on for another dish. Yum! The side of the fries that was touching the baking sheet got darkly caramelized, giving the fries a nice depth of flavor. In all honesty, they looked burnt when I first pulled them out of the oven, but tasting them quickly did away with that impression. The sugar-and-cayenne-pepper combo is a favorite of mine on other items... nice to know that it works so well on sweet potatoes!

Rating: 3
This side dish lives up to its name. I have already made it a multiple times this summer. It also works well in the oven. It is a crowd pleaser and a great subsitute for normal fries or baked potatoes.